---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CV | Vincenzo Di Perna"
  description="CV of Vincenzo Di Perna, Blockchain Systems & Digital Assets Engineer."
  sideBarActiveItemID="cv"
>
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">CV</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-90">
      I am a Blockchain Systems & Digital Assets Engineer with a PhD in
      Blockchain & DLT, focused on distributed systems, blockchain benchmarking,
      reproducible experimentation, protocol evaluation, data analysis, and
      digital-asset infrastructures.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a
        class="btn btn-primary"
        href="/cv/Di_Perna_CV.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Download CV
      </a>

      <a
        class="btn btn-outline"
        href="https://github.com/vindipe"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        GitHub
      </a>

      <a
        class="btn btn-outline"
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/vincenzo-di-perna/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        LinkedIn
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Profile</h2>

    <div class="text-justify leading-relaxed">
      <p class="mb-4">
        My work combines distributed systems research, experimental methodology,
        blockchain infrastructure evaluation, and data-driven analysis. During
        my PhD, I designed and used reproducible benchmarking pipelines to study
        how blockchain systems behave under different workloads, network
        topologies, and operational conditions.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        I am particularly interested in performance and latency evaluation,
        energy efficiency, repeatability, performance predictability, protocol
        analytics, digital-asset and CBDC-related infrastructures, and research
        engineering practices that make experimental results easier to reproduce
        and compare.
      </p>

      <p>
        I am open to engineering, R&D, data, research, and hybrid roles where
        rigorous experimentation, distributed systems knowledge, and
        blockchain/digital-asset expertise can support practical technical
        decisions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Education</h2>

    <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4">
      <TimeLineElement
        title="PhD in Blockchain & Distributed Ledger Technology"
        subtitle="Università di Camerino, Italy"
        date="2022–2025"
      >
        Dissertation focused on comparing blockchain systems across performance,
        energy, repeatability, predictability, and economic-efficiency
        dimensions. Research included topology-aware benchmarking, reproducible
        experimentation, workload design, network emulation, and statistical
        analysis of blockchain system behavior.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="MSc in ICT Solutions Architect"
        subtitle="Università di Pisa, Italy"
        date="2019–2022"
      >
        Graduate studies focused on ICT architectures, software systems,
        networks, security, and technical design of digital infrastructures.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="BSc in Computer Systems and Network Security"
        subtitle="Università degli Studi di Milano, Italy"
        date="2015–2019"
      >
        Foundation in computer systems, operating systems, networks,
        cybersecurity, programming, and technical problem solving.
      </TimeLineElement>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Certifications</h2>

    <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4">
      <TimeLineElement
        title="Blockchain for Business Certificate"
        subtitle="SUPSI / USI / Franklin University Switzerland / City of Lugano"
        date="2023"
        variant="warning"
      >
        Professional certificate focused on blockchain applications, business
        use cases, digital-asset-related innovation, and the connection between
        blockchain technologies, institutions, and real-world business contexts.
      </TimeLineElement>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">
      Research & Engineering Experience
    </h2>

    <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4">
      <TimeLineElement
        title="Blockchain Benchmarking & Distributed Systems Research"
        subtitle="PhD research and related research"
      >
        Designed, executed, and analyzed reproducible blockchain experiments
        across multiple platforms, workloads, and network conditions. Evaluated
        throughput, latency, energy usage, variability, repeatability, and
        performance predictability under controlled experimental settings.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Lilith — Topology-Aware Blockchain Benchmarking Framework"
        subtitle="Research artifact and experimental toolchain"
      >
        Built a benchmarking framework integrating blockchain workload
        generation, network emulation, orchestration, and data analysis. Used it
        to study how topology and workload interactions affect blockchain
        performance and energy behavior.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Digital Assets & CBDC-Oriented Data Workflows"
        subtitle="Protocol analytics, dashboards, and structured data analysis"
      >
        Worked on data-oriented analysis and dashboard concepts for digital
        assets, digital-asset and CBDC-related infrastructures, and blockchain
        ecosystem indicators, connecting technical protocol behavior with
        analytical and economic perspectives.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Research Engineering & Reproducibility"
        subtitle="Software artifacts, datasets, pipelines, and experimental methodology"
      >
        Developed scripts, datasets, reproducible workflows, statistical
        analyses, and documentation to support repeatable experiments and
        transparent evaluation of blockchain systems.
      </TimeLineElement>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Publications</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div
            class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2"
          >
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Impact of Network Topologies on Blockchain Performance
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">ACM DEBS '25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Marco Bernardo, Francesco Fabris, Sebastião
            Amaro, Miguel Matos, and Valerio Schiavoni.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Proceedings of the 19th ACM International Conference on Distributed
            and Event-Based Systems, 2025.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3701717.3730540"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              DOI / Paper
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div
            class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2"
          >
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Blockchain Energy Consumption: Unveiling the Impact of Network
              Topologies
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">IEEE ICBC '25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Valerio Schiavoni, Francesco Fabris, and Marco
            Bernardo.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Proceedings of the 2025 IEEE International Conference on Blockchain
            and Cryptocurrency.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11114569"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              IEEE Xplore
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div
            class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2"
          >
            <h3 class="card-title">
              An Entropy-Based Approach to Evaluating the Economic Efficiency of
              Cryptocurrencies
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">DLT '25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Michele Foderaro, Francesco Fabris, and Marco
            Bernardo.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Distributed Ledger Technology Workshop, CEUR Workshop Proceedings,
            Vol. 4105, 2025.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-4105/paper09.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              CEUR paper
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div
            class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2"
          >
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Dynamic Taxonomy: A Bridge from DeFi to TradFi
            </h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">SSRN</span>
              <span class="badge badge-outline shrink-0"
                >CCAF collaboration</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            Iqbal Mabruri, Carles Cerqueda, Christopher Jack, Alexis Lui, Yue
            Wu, Wenbin Wu, Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Keith Bear, and Bryan Zheng
            Zhang.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            SSRN working paper developed in collaboration with the Cambridge
            Centre for Alternative Finance (CCAF), focused on digital assets,
            decentralized finance, traditional finance, and taxonomy-oriented
            analysis.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=5034378"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              SSRN
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Tools & Artifacts</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Lilith</h3>
          <p>
            Topology-aware blockchain benchmarking framework integrating
            workload generation, network emulation, orchestration, and
            experiment analysis.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.11409100"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              Zenodo artifact
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Blockchain Repeatability Dataset</h3>
          <p>
            Dataset and repeated experimental campaign for studying blockchain
            performance variability, repeatability, and predictability.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15545963"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              Zenodo dataset
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Technical Skills</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Programming, scripting & automation</h3>

          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>
              Python for orchestration, data processing, experiment automation,
              and analysis workflows
            </li>
            <li>
              Bash scripting for Linux automation, reproducible runs, and
              command-line pipelines
            </li>
            <li>
              Rust familiarity for systems-oriented programming and low-level
              software concepts
            </li>
            <li>
              JavaScript / TypeScript basics for web interfaces, personal-site
              tooling, and frontend integration
            </li>
            <li>
              Familiarity with Go, C, and C++ from systems, networking, and
              academic contexts
            </li>
            <li>
              Git, GitHub, branching, pull requests, repository organization,
              and basic CI workflows
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Data analysis, statistics & visualization</h3>

          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>
              Structured analysis of benchmark outputs, logs, experimental
              traces, and performance datasets
            </li>
            <li>
              Throughput, latency, energy, variability, repeatability, and
              predictability metrics
            </li>
            <li>
              Statistical reasoning for experimental comparison, including ANOVA
              and ICC-style variance analysis
            </li>
            <li>
              Data cleaning, aggregation, transformation, and reproducible
              analysis pipelines
            </li>
            <li>
              Python-based analytics with notebooks, scripts, CSV/JSON
              processing, and publication-ready figures
            </li>
            <li>
              Dashboard-style visual analytics for protocol, digital-asset, and
              infrastructure indicators
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Distributed systems & infrastructure</h3>

          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>
              Linux-based development, debugging, scripting, and experimental
              execution environments
            </li>
            <li>
              Docker-based deployment, containerized experiments, and
              reproducible software environments
            </li>
            <li>
              Network emulation and controlled experimental topologies for
              distributed-system evaluation
            </li>
            <li>
              Benchmark orchestration across multiple nodes, workloads,
              platforms, and configurations
            </li>
            <li>
              Understanding of latency, bandwidth, topology effects,
              coordination, consensus, and system variability
            </li>
            <li>
              Experience designing experiments inspired by geo-distributed
              infrastructures and cloud regions
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Blockchain, DLT & digital assets</h3>

          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>
              Blockchain benchmarking, protocol evaluation, and empirical
              comparison of DLT platforms
            </li>
            <li>
              Performance and latency analysis across consensus protocols,
              workloads, and network conditions
            </li>
            <li>
              Energy-efficiency evaluation and normalized energy-per-transaction
              analysis
            </li>
            <li>
              Experience with EVM-style systems, permissioned BFT systems,
              public PoS platforms, and experimental blockchain stacks
            </li>
            <li>
              Digital-asset analytics, DeFi/CBDC-related research context, and
              protocol-level data interpretation
            </li>
            <li>
              Interest in RWA, tokenization, ownership models, economic
              efficiency, and fairer value distribution
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">
            Benchmarking & reproducible experimentation
          </h3>

          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>
              Design of repeatable experimental campaigns across blockchain
              platforms, workloads, and topologies
            </li>
            <li>
              Integration of workload generation, network emulation,
              orchestration, monitoring, and analysis steps
            </li>
            <li>
              Use of repeated runs to study variability, worst-case deviations,
              repeatability, and predictability
            </li>
            <li>
              Experiment documentation, artifact preparation, datasets, scripts,
              and reproducibility-oriented workflows
            </li>
            <li>
              Awareness of measurement limitations, confounding factors,
              environmental control, and methodological caveats
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">
            Research engineering & technical communication
          </h3>

          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>
              Translation of research questions into executable experiments,
              metrics, datasets, and evaluation pipelines
            </li>
            <li>
              Technical writing for papers, reports, documentation,
              reproducibility packages, and research artifacts
            </li>
            <li>
              Preparation of figures, tables, methodological explanations, and
              evidence-based technical narratives
            </li>
            <li>
              Cross-domain communication across distributed systems, blockchain
              infrastructure, digital assets, and economic analysis
            </li>
            <li>
              Personal-site and portfolio development with Astro, Tailwind CSS,
              HTML/CSS, and GitHub Pages
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
